# JavaScript Workspace Build

Build and typecheck the JS workspace separately from the native app.

- Requires Node.js 22+ (Rolldown CLI uses Node 22+ APIs).
- Install dependencies once: `pnpm install` (run inside `js/`)
- Build JS runtime and example Deck App packages: `pnpm --dir js build`
- Typecheck only: `pnpm --dir js tsc`
- Lint: `pnpm --dir js lint`; format: `pnpm --dir js format`

Outputs:
- Bundled files are written to `js/dist/`.
- `js/dist/runtime/runtime.js` is the VitaDeck runtime bundle.
- Each example builds to `js/examples/<name>/dist/<name>.vdapp/` (and `.vdapp.zip`).
- During native builds, CMake copies `js/dist/runtime` to `<build>/js/`.

`vitadeck` CLI (`@vitadeck/sdk`):
- The **`vitadeck`** binary points at **`js/packages/sdk/dist/cli.mjs`** (Rolldown-built ESM). Source lives under **`js/packages/sdk/cli/`** (`cli.ts`, `copy-templates.ts`, run via **`tsx`** during **`build:cli`**); config at **`js/packages/sdk/rolldown.cli.config.mjs`**; **`js/packages/sdk/dist/`** is gitignored like `js/dist/`.
- **`pnpm --dir js install`** runs the workspace **`prepare`** script, which runs **`pnpm --filter @vitadeck/sdk run build`** (clean **`dist/`**, **`tsc`** library emit, then **`build:cli`**: Rolldown bundle + copy **`cli/templates`** → **`dist/templates`**, skipping **`node_modules`** / **`dist`** under the scaffold template).
- **`pnpm --dir js build`** runs **`pnpm --filter @vitadeck/sdk build`**, which typechecks with **`tsc`** then **`build:cli`**, so examples can run **`vitadeck build`** afterward.
- After changing **`cli/cli.ts`**, **`cli/templates/`**, or **`rolldown.cli.config.mjs`**, rebuild the CLI with **`pnpm --filter @vitadeck/sdk build:cli`** (or full **`pnpm --filter @vitadeck/sdk build`**).

Notes:
- The CMake target `js_build` calls `pnpm build:prod` in `js/`.
- On native runs, the executable in `out/vitadeck` loads `out/js/runtime.js`. Deck Apps must be installed under `out/vitadeck-data/installed-deck-apps/` (Runtime Upload or manual staging).
